There was definitely a conscious effort to evoke a strong essence of cat in her design. Physically you have her whiskers, her little stubby eyebrows, her big clumsy cat paws.
The suit kinda looks like those suits people stick cats in for funny photos, her suit has buttons where her six nipples would be, the "tail" on her head.
Then there is her behavior, her body movement, how she interacts with the human, her relative size, how she's picked up, the author using cat memes for both the cover and back of the manga.
She has a very simple design and admittedly looks more "human" than the other characters like the lion or mandrill, and honestly a lot of cat anthros...but she still looks extremely catlike that is unique.
I think it's because she constantly looks like she is being propped up by invisible hands. As if the artist had someone hold up his cat to draw her posture and silhouette when standing.

The artist also isn't afraid to switch up how her face looks in some panels which helps her either look more like a cat or a human depending on what kind of emotion he wants to get across.
If this ever gets animated this aspect of her will be lost in translation and her face will be too rigid and not expressive/cartoony/dynamic. I know it.

I like her design a lot despite it looking like just another kemono cat design
